      "side": 0,
      "message": "I believe this should not be a problem.  In the past, we got screen rotate commands that would be processed as onLayout callbacks to the extended-window which would result in the device rotation being updated in response to a layout change, and as I understand, we wanted to block the additional layout after the device update.\n\nNow that all rotations are done by setting the rotation of the model, and letting that flow through to a relayout as necessary, we shouldn\u0027t need to block these.  The virtual sensors page no longer registers a layout listener on the extended window.\n\n...And I believe I\u0027ve tested all of the various ways to initialize and change the coarse orientation.  I\u0027ve attached a debugger and verified that we only get one call to EMulatorQtWindow::rotateSkin for all the ways I\u0027m aware of to change the coarse orientation (tool window rotate buttons, virtual-sensor-page buttons, accel-widget rotation, rotation-sliders rotation, console rotate command, console set accelerometer).  If there are any other tests that you would recommend I\u0027d be happy to try those as well.",
